1.5 cups wheat flour 🌾

2/3 cup water (knead a hard dough)
Cook it on tawa as shown, add a little ghee or oil while cooking.

Carrot 🥕soup with corn & capsicum 😍
Baarish me soup ka mazza hi alag hai #monsoonfood 

LIKE & SAVE KARLO FOR LATER

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
2 chopped onions 
4 medium sized chopped carrots 🥕 
2.5 cups water
2 chopped green chillies
3-4 pepper corns 
2-3 cloves
6-7 garlic cloves 
1 tbsp chopped ginger
1 tsp salt (as per taste)
1 tsp oil
1/2 tsp black pepper powder
1/3 cup chopped capsicum 🫑 
2/3 cup sweet corn 🌽 
Add water if required (to adjust consistency) & bring the soup to a boil.
You can always adjust the quantity of green chillies, ginger & garlic as per your taste. :)

Jaldi se try karo…this tastes soo good & it’s super comforting too! 😇

Pretty Pink Hummus aka Beetroot Hummus 😄💞 #healthyfoodchoices 

LIKE & SAVE KARLO TO TRY LATER

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
1.5 cups boiled chickpeas (soak overnight & pressure cook until super soft & mushy)
5-6 garlic cloves 
1 green chilli 
2 tbsp lemon 🍋 juice
1 tsp black pepper powder 
1/3 cup roasted sesame seeds (or use tahini)
1 tsp salt (as per taste)
1 tsp roasted cumin powder
1 boiled beetroot 
1/3 cup olive oil
4 tbsp chickpea stock
2 ice cubes 
Blend until you get a smooth creamy consistency while scraping the sides with spoon at regular intervals.

Enjoy with pita bread, falafel 🧆 or in sandwiches, toastes & pasta! 😇

🍅 Tomato Rasam for this perfect weather! 🌧 #comfortfood 

LIKE & SAVE IT TO TRY LATER 

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
1 tbsp oil
1 tsp mustard seeds 
1/2 tsp cumin seeds 
Handful of curry leaves 🍃 
Pinch of hing / asafoetida
1/3 tsp turmeric powder 
2 tsp (garlic + green chilli + black pepper) fresh paste 
2 medium chopped tomatoes 🍅 
1.5 tbsp rasam powder 
1 tsp red chilli powder
1 tsp salt (as per taste)
Concentrated water of a small piece of tamarind/imli (soaked for half an hour)
Handful of chopped coriander leaves 
500 ml water (approx 3 cups)
Again add 1 tsp freshly crushed paste (garlic, green chilli, black pepper)
1/2 tsp jaggery powder (optional but preferable)

Do try out this simple recipe…trust me you are going to love it..! 😇
Goes well with rice 🍚 & can also have it just like a soup 🥣

Tadke Wali Khichdi🔥 #comfortmeal #happymonsoon 

LIKE & SAVE KARLO TO TRY LATER

You all know my love for khichdi & how I like experimenting new recipes of the same!
Amongst all this one is surely one of my most favourite. 

👩‍🍳 INGREDIENTS :
2 tbsp oil
1 tsp cumin seeds 
1 tsp ajwain / carom seeds
Handful of peanuts 🥜 (soak in water for 15mins)
1/3 tsp hing / asafoetida 
2 tsp finely chopped green/regular garlic
1/2 capsicum 🫑 (add any veggies of choice)
1/3 cup green peas 
1/3 cup valor papdi daana / flat beans (optional, if available do add)
2 small whole onions 🧅
1 cup rice + 1.5 cups toor dal (soak both for 1hour)
4 cups of water (as per required consistency)
1 tsp salt 🧂 (as per taste)
2/3 tsp turmeric powder 
Cook upto 3-4 whistles 

🔥 For the tadka -
2 tbsp ghee
Handful of finely chopped garlic 🧄 
1 tsp pickle masala (or red chilli powder)

Serve this khichdi with curd, ghee, pickle & papad! 
Do try out this recipe soon & let me know how you guys liked it… 😇

Pineapple🍍 Panna / Ananas ka Panna #summerrecipe 

LIKE & SAVE KARLO TO TRY LATER

It’s sweet, mildly spiced, little tangy & absolutely refreshing! A must try in this season. 👌🏻

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
1 whole pineapple 🍍
1 cup water
2/3 tsp salt
1/3 cup sugar
1/2 black salt
2/3 tsp red chili powder (add less if making for kids) alternatively you can also add 1 slit green chilli 
1/3 tsp turmeric 
1 tsp roasted cumin powder 
Half a lemon 🍋 juice
The concentrate of pineapple panna purée can be stored in an air tight container & refrigerated for upto 15-20days.

🍹 For serving, take few ice cubes in a glass, add few mint leaves 🍃 , about 4-5tbsp of the panna concentrate & 2/3 cup of chilled water. 
Enjoyyy…!! 😍

Aam panna toh bohot piya hoga, this year try out this version of panna..
This panna helps in good immunity, digestion & improves hair and skin.

Protein Packed Sprouts Dosa 💚
~ Tasty, wholesome & a perfect breakfast option! ✨

SAVE IT TO TRY SOON

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
1 cup mix sprouts (kala chana + green moong)
2 green chilies 
1 inch ginger 🫚 
8-10 curry leaves 🍃 
2 tsp cumin seeds
1.5 tsp salt (as per taste)
2/3 cup sooji
1/2 cup chopped coriander leaves 
3-4 tbsp curd 
1/2 cup water (add gradually as per requirement)
Blend everything well to form a smooth batter

🥙 For Stuffing :
1/2 cup finely chopped onion 🧅 
1/2 cup finely chopped red bell pepper 
(Add any veggies of choice)
150g low fat paneer
Salt & black pepper (as per taste)

Heat the dosa tawa, sprinkle few drops of water, rub half cut onion on the tawa. Make dosa as shown in the video! 

Serve with any dip or chutney of choice! 😇

Healthier version : Chipotle Paneer 🥪 
~ A perfect snack time option ✨

SAVE IT TO TRY SOON

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
For the Chipotle Dip - 
150g fresh low fat paneer 
8-10 soaked cashews (soak in hot water for at least 1 hour)
2-3 spicy dry red chilies 🌶️ (soak in hot water for at least 1 hour)
1 cheese cube (optional)
2/3 tsp salt 
1 tsp oregano 
2/3 tsp kashmiri red chili powder 
1.5 tsp extra virgin olive oil 🫒 
2-3 ice cubes 🧊 
1/3 cup water (add as per requirement to adjust the consistency)
Blend everything well until you get a smooth creamy texture as shown in the video!
📌 The dip is now ready, you can store this in an air tight container & refrigerate for upto 3 days. 

For the Sandwich -
Bread slices 🍞 
Apply a generous layer of the chipotle dip on both breads, top with veggies of choice (I have used onions, capsicum 🫑 & tomato)
Sprinkle a little chaat masala on the veggies, toast the sandwich in some ghee/olive oil until crispy & golden brown on both sides. 

Serve this with some more creamy dip & enjoy! 😇

Jamun Mojito 💜

SAVE IT TO TRY SOON

👩‍🍳 Ingredients : 
Soak 150g jamun in water + 1 tsp salt for 30mins & then deseed all the jamun
6-7 mint leaves 🍃 
1/2 lemon 🍋 juice 
1/2 tsp rock salt
2-3 tbsp honey 🍯 (as per taste)
1 ice cube while making the purée concentrate & 7-8 ice cubes 🧊 in glass
Add 4-5 tbsp jamun purée & add chilled soda! 

Serve chilled & enjoy!! 😎

You can even deep freeze the jamun concentrate in bulk for over a month. 
Use in ice golas or make refreshing mocktails… 🍹

Healthier Version : Red Sauce Pasta 🍝 
~ Packed with flavours, sneaked in veggies & some protein for a balanced meal ✨

SAVE IT TO TRY SOON

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
1 tsp oil
3-4 tomatoes 🍅 
1 red bell pepper 
7-8 garlic cloves
1/2 tsp salt
1 tbsp water
Cook until tomatoes become mushy & the skin can be peeled off easily 

👉🏻 For the sauce -
Add all the cooked veggies
100g low fat paneer (crumbled)
1 tsp peri peri masala
1/2 tsp salt
2-3 ice cubes
Blend everything into a smooth sauce!

Now take 1 tsp chilli oil/olive oil in a pan, add the prepared sauce along with some fresh basil leaves 🍃, cook it for a minute & add cooked pasta(I have used Emmer wheat fusilli pasta) with some pasta water, give it a quick gentle mix & serve hot! 🥰

Stuffed Parwal Aloo 💚

SAVE IT TO TRY SOON

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
250g parwal wash and soak in water for 15mins. Scrap the hard part of it’s outer peel as shown & insert a slit to add the stuffing.
2 small potatoes 🥔 (cut into slices & soak in water)

For the stuffing -
2.5 tbsp besan 
2 tsp cumin-coriander powder 
2 tsp red chilli powder 🌶️ 
2/3 tsp turmeric powder 
1 tsp garam masala
2 tbsp roasted & crushed peanuts 🥜 
2 tbsp chopped coriander leaves 🍃 
1 tbsp curd 
1 tsp salt 🧂 
Add a few drops of water (only if required)

Stuff each parwal with little stuffing & keep aside.

Heat 2 tbsp oil in a pan
1 tsp mustard seeds 
1 tsp cumin seeds 
1 tbsp ginger-green chilli paste (freshly crushed)
Purée of 2 tomatoes 🍅 
1 tsp salt (as per taste)
1/2 tsp red chilli powder 
1/3 tsp turmeric powder 
Add the remaining stuffing with 1cup water 
Add potatoes & stuffed parwal
Cover & cook for 20-22mins on medium flame until everything is cooked (stir in between)
Finally garnish with fresh coriander 🌿 

Serve hot with roti/paratha or rice! 😇

Delicious Fruity Custard! 🍮🥭
Looking for a quick, healthy & super tasty summer treat for the kids?? ✨

Try these Fruity Custard Cups made with Gritzo Vanilla SuperMilk — packed with protein, nutrients and creamy deliciousness!

👩‍🍳 Recipe :
Soak some dry fruits , rolled oats & saffron strands in warm milk. 🥛 
Add 2 scoops of Gritzo Vanilla SuperMilk to the soaked ingredients & blend everything well.
Add 1tsp honey 🍯 for extra sweetness! (Optional)
 Cool to room temperature , then refrigerate for atleast 30mins.
In small cups/glasses, layer fresh fruits like banana, mangoe & pomegranate. 🍌 🥭
Pour the chilled SuperMilk mix over the fruits – it turns into a creamy custard!
Garnish with seeds, dry fruits, granola or more fresh fruits.

❄️ Serve chilled and watch the kids love every spoon!
Healthy, yummy & perfect for post-playtime snacks!

Delicious Basundi, The Ultimate Indian Dessert! 💛
Creamy, rich and made effortless with Milkmaid – this summer treat is a total mood-fixer 😍
Made with a twist, done the Milkmaid way!
Try it, chill it, love it! ✨

👩‍🍳 Ingredients :
1.5 litres of full fat milk
10-12 saffron strands soaked in 3tbsp warm milk
300ml Nestlé Milkmaid
1/3 cup chopped nuts (almonds & pistachios)
1 tsp cardamom powder 

🧡 For more such recipe inspiration : www.milkmaid.in
📸 Don’t forget to tag me & @milkmaidindia – we’d love to see your version! #IMilkmaidIt 🫶🏼

Summer Special : Masala Chaach 💚
~ Approx 9g protein under 110 calories ✨

SAVE IT TO TRY SOON

👩‍🍳 Ingredients : {serves 2}
3.5 tbsp Chana (mildly dry roaated. You can alternatively use sattu aswell) 
1 green chilli 
8-10 pudina / mint 🍃 
Handful of coriander leaves 
1/2 cup fresh curd or yogurt 
1 tsp Himalayan pink salt
1.5 tsp roasted cumin powder 
1.5 cup cold water (add as per consistency required)

Soak 1tsp basil seeds in 1/3 cup water for 15mins. 

Enjoy this refreshing, flavourful & gut friendly buttermilk chilled! 😇
